The paper describes a library for similarity searching, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB). The library focuses on search methods for non-metric spaces, which are often used in machine learning (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). The paper also discusses efficiency-effectiveness trade-offs, which is a topic in both machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
